6. THE SEPARATION FIREWALL

6.1 The Orbital-Terrestrial Communication Protocol

Earth → Orbit (Uplink):

· Format: Signed queries with cryptographic nonce
· Content: Questions, data for analysis, system updates
· Authentication: NASAg-signed certificates required
· Bandwidth: High (100 Gbps aggregate)

Orbit → Earth (Downlink):

· Format: Spectrum analysis results
· Content: Multiple perspectives, divergence maps
· Authentication: Constellation-signed with proof of processing
· Bandwidth: Limited (1 Gbps aggregate)
· Latency: Minimum 100ms (deliberate)

Emergency Channels:

· Quantum-secured command override (Earth → Orbit only)
· Kill-switch activation (requires 5-of-7 NASAg approval)
· Constellation isolation mode (complete radio silence)

6.2 The Energy Independence Principle

Orbital Energy System:

· Power Source: 100% solar (triple-junction GaAs cells)
· Storage: Flywheel energy storage (no chemical batteries)
· Redundancy: N+3 design (can lose 3 satellites per plane)
· Efficiency: >40% conversion, waste heat radiated to space

Terrestrial Energy Constraints:

· Monitoring: Real-time power consumption telemetry
· Limits: Licensed maximum power draw
· Location: Grid-tied with backup limitations
· Efficiency: Minimum performance per watt standards

No Shared Infrastructure:

· Separate manufacturing chains
· Separate maintenance protocols
· Separate disposal/recycling
· No common vulnerabilities

