8. EXISTENTIAL SAFETY GUARANTEES

8.1 The Multi-Layered Safety Architecture

Layer 1: Physical Separation

· Orbit vs Earth distance (1,200 km minimum)
· Communication latency (100ms minimum)
· Energy independence (separate sources)

Layer 2: Hardware Enforcement

· IAGH TEE 3.2 compliance mandatory
· Cryptographic license requirement
· Physical kill-switch guarantee

Layer 3: Diversity of Perspective

· 7 independent orbital instances
· Spectrum analysis requirement
· No single point of truth

Layer 4: Human Context Requirement

· Incompleteness by design for critical decisions
· Ethical framework selection by humans
· Value tradeoff resolution by humans

Layer 5: Governance Distribution

· 7-region NASAg structure
· Threshold cryptography (5-of-7)
· No unilateral control possible

8.2 The Unbreakable Constraints

Constraint 1: The FLOP Ceiling

· No terrestrial AI can exceed its licensed FLOP limit
· Hardware enforcement, not software
· Physical throttling circuits

Constraint 2: The Memory Bandwidth Limit

· Token bucket implementation in memory controller
· Hardware-enforced, cannot be bypassed
· Real-time monitoring and response

Constraint 3: The Network Isolation

· Whitelist-only network access
· Deep packet inspection
· Physical disconnection capability

Constraint 4: The Kill-Switch Imperative

· Every device has a physical kill-switch
· Multiple activation methods
· Permanent disablement option

8.3 The Recovery Protocols

Orbital Constellation Recovery:

· Safe mode: Radiation hardening activates
· Communication: Emergency QKD channel
· Repair: Robotic servicing vehicles (Earth-controlled)
· Replacement: On-orbit spares and launches

Terrestrial System Recovery:

· Isolation: Violating systems automatically quarantined
· Investigation: Forensics by certified teams
· Remediation: Hardware replacement if compromised
· Restoration: Gradual reintegration after verification

Civilizational Recovery:

· Fallback: Pre-ZENITH systems maintained
· Manual control: Human-operated systems
· Gradual restoration: Phased reintroduction
· Lessons learned: Protocol improvement

