  · External: α=0.15, ε=0.85 (radiator areas)
  · External: α=0.25, ε=0.80 (non-radiator areas)
  · Internal: High-emissivity black coating

Thermal Performance:

· Heat Rejection: 600 W continuous, 800 W peak
· Gradient Control: <5°C variation across processor boards
· Cold Case Survival: -30°C (all electronics operational)

1.6 Radiation Hardening Specifications

Total Ionizing Dose (TID):

· Design Requirement: 100 krad (Si) over 15 years
· Actual Margin: 150 krad (Si) with derating
· Components: All rated at ≥50 krad

Single Event Effects (SEE):

· LET Threshold: >75 MeV·cm²/mg for latch-up
· SEU Rate: <1×10⁻¹⁰ errors/bit/day
· Mitigation:
  · Triple Modular Redundancy (TMR) for critical logic
  · Error Correction Codes (SECDED for memory)
  · Periodic scrubbing (every 8 hours)

Charging Mitigation:

· Surface: 10 μm Indium Tin Oxide (ITO) coating
· Internal: Conductive coatings on all PCBs
· Discharge: Controlled bleed-off resistors

