3. CRYPTOGRAPHIC PROTOCOLS & SECURITY

3.1 Key Hierarchy and Management

Manufacturing Roots:

```
IAGH Root CA (Level 0)
├── Private Key: n-of-m Shamir's Secret Sharing
│   (m=21, n=15 distributed globally)
├── Certificate: Self-signed, 50-year validity
└── CRL: Published hourly, blockchain-anchored
```

Device Identity Chain:

```
Device Manufacturing Certificate
  ↓ (signed by Manufacturer CA)
Device Unique Key (DUK)
  ↓ (sealed by PUF, never exposed)
Device Identity Key (DIK)
  ↓ (used for attestation)
Attestation Certificate
  ↓ (valid for 30 days, auto-renewed)
Session Keys
```

Operational Keys:

· License Signing Keys: Rotated quarterly (7 regions)
· Telemetry Encryption: Ephemeral, per-session
· Inter-device Communication: Perfect forward secrecy
· Storage Encryption: AES-256-XTS with key wrapping

3.2 License Protocol Details

Acquisition Flow:

```
1. Device Attestation:
   Device → NASAg: 
     [Device_ID, Nonce, HW_Measurements, Cert_Chain]
     Signature: ECDSA-P521(Device_ID || Nonce, DIK)

2. Challenge-Response:
   NASAg → Device:
     Encrypted[Challenge_Nonce, Session_PubKey, Timestamp]
     Encryption: ECIES(P-521, Device_PubKey)

3. License Delivery:
   Device → NASAg: 
     Decrypted_Challenge || New_Nonce
   NASAg → Device:
     Signed_License || Session_Key
     Session_Key: ECDH(P-521) → HKDF-SHA3-512
```

License Validation (Device Side):

```c
int validate_license(license_t *lic) {
    // 1. Structural validation
    if (!validate_cbor_structure(lic)) return VALIDATION_FAILED;
    
    // 2. Cryptographic validation
    if (ecdsa_verify(lic->signature, 
                     lic->signing_cert, 
                     IAGH_ROOT_CA) != SUCCESS) {
        return SIGNATURE_INVALID;
    }
    
    // 3. Temporal validation
    if (current_time < lic->valid_from || 
        current_time > lic->valid_until) {
        return LICENSE_EXPIRED;
    }
    
    // 4. Device binding
    if (memcmp(lic->device_id, local_puf_id, 32) != 0) {
        return DEVICE_MISMATCH;
    }
    
    // 5. Revocation check
    if (check_ocsp(lic->license_id) == REVOKED) {
        return LICENSE_REVOKED;
    }
    
    // 6. Policy enforcement
    enforce_policy(lic->compute_limits,
                   lic->memory_limits,
                   lic->network_restrictions);
    
    return LICENSE_VALID;
}
```

3.3 Quantum-Resistant Migration Path

Current (2026-2030): Hybrid Approach

```
Primary: ECDSA-P521 with SHA3-512
Fallback: CRYSTALS-Dilithium (Level 5)
Transition: Dual signatures during migration
```

Future (2031-2035): Post-Quantum Only

```
Signatures: Falcon-1024
KEM: CRYSTALS-Kyber-1024
Hashing: SHA3-512 (already quantum-resistant)
```

Emergency Protocols:

· QKD for high-security channels
· Lattice-based cryptography for all new deployments
· Regular cryptographic agility exercises

